Moreover, we plan to extend our framework to tackle more complex gait analysis tasks, such as identifying specific gait patterns associated with different neurological disorders and developing personalized gait rehabilitation plans.

To achieve these goals, we will first investigate the optimal fusion strategies for combining the visual, audio, and IMU data to improve the robustness of the gait parameter estimation. This will involve evaluating different feature extraction and fusion techniques, such as convolutional neural networks (CNNs), recurrent neural networks (RNNs), and attention mechanisms.

We will also explore the use of transfer learning and pre-trained models to leverage the knowledge gained from large datasets in computer vision and natural language processing. Additionally, we will investigate the impact of data augmentation and normalization techniques on the performance of the fusion strategies and the robustness of the gait parameter estimation.

This will be achieved through a combination of theoretical analysis and experimental evaluation, where we will assess the effectiveness of different fusion approaches and techniques on various gait-related tasks, such as gait recognition, gait analysis, and fall detection.

This comprehensive evaluation will be conducted through a systematic methodology, involving the development of a novel gait dataset, the implementation of various machine learning algorithms, and the utilization of advanced sensors and motion capture systems to collect and analyze the necessary data.

The dataset will consist of a large number of participants with varying levels of mobility and gait abnormalities, collected over a prolonged period of time to capture the complexity of human gait in different contexts and conditions.

This will enable the development of a robust machine learning model that can accurately identify and classify gait patterns, allowing for the detection of subtle changes in mobility and early signs of gait disorders, ultimately informing the development of personalized interventions and rehabilitation strategies for individuals with mobility impairments.
